Returns the whole exception flags. The following is an example of how to use these exceptions related methods *Pipepi;
*
*bitset<DevicePipeBlob::numFlags>bs=pi.exceptions();
*cout<<"bs="<<bs<<endl;
*
*pi.set_exceptions(DevicePipeBlob::wrongtype_flag);
*bs=pi.exceptions();
*
*cout<<"bs="<<bs<<endl;
*

